# The Codex

This application functions as an archive, a catalogue of important elements of a fictional world.

It has the following main features:

- Catalogue entries from a given set of documents to create a new codex
- Update the codex based on new documents
- Answer questions about the codex

The codex files are used by the following applications:

- **Codex**: this application maintains the files.
- **Backlog Saga**:
  - This application reads the files and uses them to ground the LLM to be aware of the world.
  - It also adds new entries to the codex.
  - In the future, it may also allow the user to browse through the codex like a wiki.
- **Oath Simulator**: This setup (now in Claude Cowork, maybe a separate application in the future) uses the files to ground the bot players, and also adds new entries or updates existing ones based on how the game develops.

## Folders

A codex folder is structured as follows:

- buildings
- characters
- events
- locations
- relics

The folders contain one file per world entity.

## Cataloguing

Cataloguing is done in two phases:

- First, get the LLM to compile a list of all of these things, and set up the folder structure.
- Then, populate the folders, one at a time.

## Structure

Each file consists of the following:

- Title
- Description (~3 sentences, or ~6 sentences for important entries that occur often in the documents)
- History (~3 sentences, or ~6 sentences for important entries that occur often in the documents)
- Location (the name of a location in the locations folder, or, for a location, its region)
